1
00:00:13,545 --> 00:00:15,144
We'd seized Baan Prongdong Base for only

2
00:00:15,145 --> 00:00:16,504
a few days before it was overrun.

3
00:00:16,505 --> 00:00:18,984
We can’t even hold a base this small.

4
00:00:18,985 --> 00:00:21,065
So how are we supposed to protect the whole country?

5
00:00:21,585 --> 00:00:24,545
If we let this drag on, they’ll only grow more confident.

6
00:00:25,545 --> 00:00:27,825
How far have you gotten inside their inner circle?

7
00:00:29,585 --> 00:00:31,025
I just need a little more time, sir.

8
00:00:32,385 --> 00:00:33,864
We’re out of time!

9
00:00:33,865 --> 00:00:35,544
Orders have come down that we must take down-

10
00:00:35,545 --> 00:00:37,104
-Baan Saeng Dao base.

11
00:00:37,105 --> 00:00:39,745
This has dragged on far too long, Dan Din.

12
00:00:40,665 --> 00:00:43,304
But Baan Saeng Dao base isn’t just armed forces.

13
00:00:43,305 --> 00:00:45,545
There are civilians in there too, sir.

14
00:00:47,545 --> 00:00:48,545
Dan Din.

15
00:00:49,945 --> 00:00:52,225
For the peace of the entire country,

16
00:00:53,425 --> 00:00:55,785
we have to do things we don’t want to do.

17
00:00:57,985 --> 00:00:59,585
But if you’re not comfortable with this,

18
00:01:00,305 --> 00:01:02,505
you can request a transfer back to Bangkok.

19
00:01:09,265 --> 00:01:10,384
In that case,

20
00:01:10,385 --> 00:01:12,665
I’ll find a way to infiltrate Baan Saeng Dao base myself.

21
00:02:18,585 --> 00:02:20,065
Oh! Comrade Saeng.

22
00:02:21,505 --> 00:02:22,505
Bai Tong.

23
00:02:24,705 --> 00:02:25,904
You feeling better, Comrade Saeng?

24
00:02:25,905 --> 00:02:27,345
You promised to teach us basketball.

25
00:02:27,785 --> 00:02:30,344
I’m good now. Feeling great.

26
00:02:30,345 --> 00:02:31,825
Let your arm heal first.

27
00:02:32,585 --> 00:02:33,984
Don’t overuse it yet.

28
00:02:33,985 --> 00:02:35,545
How are you doing, Comrade Saeng?

29
00:02:39,905 --> 00:02:41,105
Thank you.

30
00:02:41,545 --> 00:02:44,345
For helping us take Baan Prongdong back.

31
00:02:44,985 --> 00:02:47,144
It’s not just a victory,

32
00:02:47,145 --> 00:02:50,624
but morale for all of us.

33
00:02:50,625 --> 00:02:52,985
The main base sent their praise too.

34
00:02:58,665 --> 00:03:02,025
What’s wrong, Comrade Saeng? Why aren’t you smiling?

35
00:03:03,385 --> 00:03:05,945
I just can’t.

36
00:03:07,905 --> 00:03:12,145
If we don’t kill them, they’ll kill us.

37
00:03:15,185 --> 00:03:17,665
If you’re this soft, maybe you shouldn’t be fighting.

38
00:03:18,785 --> 00:03:20,504
Comrade Fah.

39
00:03:20,505 --> 00:03:22,665
It’s Comrade Saeng’s first time in the battle.

40
00:03:25,625 --> 00:03:27,744
Keep indulging him like this,

41
00:03:27,745 --> 00:03:29,225
and we'd all be damed.

42
00:03:33,745 --> 00:03:36,945
Learn how to sympathize for once, Comrade Fah.

43
00:03:38,425 --> 00:03:40,585
Not everything revolves around you.

44
00:04:02,905 --> 00:04:04,464
I want to visit Yaguar's mother.

45
00:04:04,465 --> 00:04:05,345
Wanna come with?

46
00:04:05,346 --> 00:04:07,304
Comrade Roong, heading back?

47
00:04:07,305 --> 00:04:08,305
I’ll go too.

48
00:04:08,985 --> 00:04:10,464
I need to finish writing my article.

49
00:04:10,465 --> 00:04:11,465
Go ahead.

50
00:04:18,465 --> 00:04:19,544
Hey, Sila.

51
00:04:19,545 --> 00:04:20,705
Let me ask you something.

52
00:04:20,905 --> 00:04:22,784
Do you still see Mada as your girlfriend?

53
00:04:22,785 --> 00:04:26,185
You’ve been acting distant lately—like strangers.

54
00:04:26,825 --> 00:04:29,584
We came here for a cause.

55
00:04:29,585 --> 00:04:32,264
Ideals come first—love comes later.

56
00:04:32,265 --> 00:04:33,704
Don’t you remember?

57
00:04:33,705 --> 00:04:35,704
If you keep acting like this,

58
00:04:35,705 --> 00:04:37,625
how are you going to achieve anything?

59
00:04:54,865 --> 00:04:55,865
Wow.

60
00:04:56,545 --> 00:04:58,905
I didn’t know we had a place this beautiful here, Bai Tong.

61
00:04:59,065 --> 00:05:00,065
Yeah.

62
00:05:01,705 --> 00:05:03,384
This is one of our secret bases.

63
00:05:03,385 --> 00:05:06,465
Only trusted people are allowed in.

64
00:05:09,345 --> 00:05:10,945
Comrade Bai Tong, Comrade Saeng.

65
00:05:20,145 --> 00:05:21,984
This is a reward for your victory,

66
00:05:21,985 --> 00:05:24,505
and for bringing everyone back safely.

67
00:05:26,745 --> 00:05:28,225
You did great, Comrade Saeng.

68
00:05:31,225 --> 00:05:32,185
Comrade Bai Tong.

69
00:05:32,186 --> 00:05:33,344
Hmm?

70
00:05:33,345 --> 00:05:35,465
Can I ask for one more?

71
00:05:36,745 --> 00:05:37,865
Cause I…

72
00:05:38,825 --> 00:05:40,385
I want to give it to…

73
00:05:43,705 --> 00:05:45,345
someone… a friend.

74
00:05:46,185 --> 00:05:47,744
You can take a whole bunch if you want.

75
00:05:47,745 --> 00:05:48,945
Come on, let’s pick some.

76
00:05:49,425 --> 00:05:50,425
Yeah.

77
00:05:50,905 --> 00:05:52,864
Come with us, Comrade Saeng.

78
00:05:52,865 --> 00:05:53,745
If you’re giving it to someone,

79
00:05:53,746 --> 00:05:54,946
you should choose it yourself.

80
00:06:05,985 --> 00:06:07,345
Are you in there, Comrade Yue?

81
00:06:16,545 --> 00:06:17,545
Yeah?

82
00:06:28,825 --> 00:06:29,945
This is for you.

83
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:45,905
Thanks for taking care of me.

84
00:06:50,225 --> 00:06:51,984
Why are you giving this to me?

85
00:06:51,985 --> 00:06:55,185
If you do something good, you deserve a reward.

86
00:06:59,225 --> 00:07:01,185
Do you know what a cockscomb flower means?

87
00:07:03,545 --> 00:07:06,345
Cockscomb flower? It has a meaning?

88
00:07:07,385 --> 00:07:09,144
I’m not sure either.

89
00:07:09,145 --> 00:07:11,345
But Comrade Bai Tong gave it to me.

90
00:07:18,465 --> 00:07:20,384
Among the Hmong,

91
00:07:20,385 --> 00:07:21,905
they give cockscomb flowers to-

92
00:07:23,105 --> 00:07:24,745
someone they’re interested in.

93
00:07:28,825 --> 00:07:30,305
It means.

94
00:07:31,545 --> 00:07:32,665
“I want to get to know you,”

95
00:07:36,185 --> 00:07:37,345
“I want to talk to you.”

96
00:07:45,825 --> 00:07:47,425
Now that you know…

97
00:07:48,505 --> 00:07:49,985
Want to have it back?

98
00:07:54,345 --> 00:07:55,545
I gave it to you.

99
00:07:56,305 --> 00:07:57,425
I’m not taking it back.

100
00:08:24,905 --> 00:08:26,145
Comrade Yue!

101
00:08:27,505 --> 00:08:28,505
Comrade Yue!

102
00:08:30,305 --> 00:08:31,305
Comrade Yue!

103
00:08:31,306 --> 00:08:32,344
Yeah?

104
00:08:32,345 --> 00:08:35,304
What’s going on? Everyone else is about to collapse.

105
00:08:35,305 --> 00:08:36,545
Can we take a break?

106
00:08:37,065 --> 00:08:38,065
That's it.

107
00:08:46,545 --> 00:08:48,265
What are you looking at, Comrade Phu Pha?

108
00:08:49,065 --> 00:08:50,105
What’s wrong with you?

109
00:08:50,865 --> 00:08:51,785
Um?

110
00:08:51,786 --> 00:08:54,305
You look like your soul’s still stuck on the battlefield.

111
00:08:56,865 --> 00:08:58,064
Oh…

112
00:08:58,065 --> 00:08:59,664
If something’s on your mind, just say it.

113
00:08:59,665 --> 00:09:00,985
Why keep it bottled up?

114
00:09:02,585 --> 00:09:04,464
Ugh… sooner or later, I’m going to find out anyway.

115
00:09:04,465 --> 00:09:05,465
Just spill it.

116
00:09:06,025 --> 00:09:07,025
Come on.

117
00:09:17,225 --> 00:09:25,225
If you’ve got feelings for someone…

118
00:09:27,185 --> 00:09:29,625
but you know it shouldn’t happen,

119
00:09:30,305 --> 00:09:31,865
what would you do?

120
00:09:32,385 --> 00:09:34,985
Don’t tell me—you’ve fallen for someone?

121
00:09:36,545 --> 00:09:38,025
Hold on, man.

122
00:09:39,305 --> 00:09:41,545
If you think it’s real, then go for it.

123
00:09:42,545 --> 00:09:44,505
What, are you scared of the Three Delays Policy?

124
00:09:45,145 --> 00:09:47,665
That policy doesn’t apply to love, does it?

125
00:09:49,585 --> 00:09:50,585
I know right.

126
00:09:50,586 --> 00:09:53,105
But it’s not that simple.

127
00:09:54,945 --> 00:09:57,225
I think If you’re honest with your feelings,

128
00:09:57,985 --> 00:09:59,505
then nothing’s really that hard.

129
00:10:02,145 --> 00:10:03,984
We’re living in a battlefield.

130
00:10:03,985 --> 00:10:05,785
We could die any day.

131
00:10:06,865 --> 00:10:09,664
So if you still have the strength to love someone,

132
00:10:09,665 --> 00:10:11,544
then just love them.

133
00:10:11,545 --> 00:10:12,945
Don’t overthink it.

134
00:10:15,905 --> 00:10:16,905
Come on—.

135
00:10:18,865 --> 00:10:19,865
Go confess.

136
00:11:00,585 --> 00:11:02,304
Among the Hmong,

137
00:11:02,305 --> 00:11:04,824
they give a cockscomb flower

138
00:11:04,825 --> 00:11:06,305
to someone they’re interested in.

139
00:11:08,025 --> 00:11:09,265
It means.

140
00:11:10,745 --> 00:11:11,865
“I want to get to know you,”

141
00:11:12,665 --> 00:11:13,945
“I want to talk to you.”

142
00:11:17,465 --> 00:11:18,545
Now that you know…

143
00:11:20,185 --> 00:11:21,225
want to have it back?

144
00:11:24,785 --> 00:11:25,785
I gave it to you.

145
00:11:26,545 --> 00:11:27,545
I’m not taking it back.

146
00:12:30,505 --> 00:12:31,185
Hey!!

147
00:12:31,505 --> 00:12:33,985
Da fuck with that smile? Creepy motherfucker.

148
00:12:37,225 --> 00:12:41,104
(Music playing)
As the sunlight slowly fades away,

149
00:12:41,105 --> 00:12:45,104
all I need is someone by my side.

150
00:12:45,105 --> 00:12:49,504
Let it be you, let it be you.

151
00:12:49,505 --> 00:12:53,344
Just sitting close, meeting your eyes, warms my heart.

152
00:12:53,345 --> 00:12:57,104
Let this moment be just the two of us.

153
00:12:57,105 --> 00:13:01,184
Like the moon waiting for its time to shine.

154
00:13:01,185 --> 00:13:05,144
Let it be you, can it be you?

155
00:13:05,145 --> 00:13:09,224
The one who stays by my side and never leaves.

156
00:13:09,225 --> 00:13:13,545
Let it be you…

157
00:13:33,745 --> 00:13:37,065
This clearing just never seems to end in a large field here.

158
00:13:37,745 --> 00:13:39,825
I still haven’t finished writing my article.

159
00:13:41,105 --> 00:13:43,265
Every time we clear it, you complain.

160
00:13:44,785 --> 00:13:47,145
Work like this should be shared across all units.

161
00:13:48,185 --> 00:13:49,625
Even the villagers are helping out.

162
00:13:55,505 --> 00:13:57,145
Labor is honor.

163
00:13:58,345 --> 00:14:00,305
Did you forget what the Party taught us?

164
00:14:17,265 --> 00:14:18,145
Comrade…

165
00:14:18,146 --> 00:14:20,504
Did you do something to upset Comrade Yue?

166
00:14:20,505 --> 00:14:21,584
He keeps staring at you.

167
00:14:21,585 --> 00:14:23,025
No—nothing.

168
00:14:24,265 --> 00:14:25,265
Not at all.

169
00:14:25,625 --> 00:14:27,105
Why are you getting all high-pitched?

170
00:14:27,585 --> 00:14:28,705
That’s suspicious.

171
00:14:29,385 --> 00:14:30,385
Suspicious?

172
00:14:37,065 --> 00:14:38,065
Hey!!

173
00:14:38,066 --> 00:14:40,624
Sorry—my bad, slipped a bit.

174
00:14:40,625 --> 00:14:41,625
Hey,

175
00:14:42,665 --> 00:14:43,665
are you okay?

176
00:14:44,105 --> 00:14:44,745
Huh?

177
00:14:44,746 --> 00:14:45,865
You’re bleeding.

178
00:14:49,305 --> 00:14:50,305
Oh—.

179
00:14:50,825 --> 00:14:51,905
It’s nothing.

180
00:14:53,425 --> 00:14:54,425
Be more careful.

181
00:14:59,745 --> 00:15:01,624
Thank you, everyone,

182
00:15:01,625 --> 00:15:04,304
for working together like this.

183
00:15:04,305 --> 00:15:05,824
Preparing the soil for this year’s crops is-

184
00:15:05,825 --> 00:15:08,065
-something we all share responsibility for.

185
00:15:08,785 --> 00:15:13,945
Here, no matter your rank or position,

186
00:15:15,025 --> 00:15:17,025
everyone is equal.

187
00:15:18,945 --> 00:15:20,705
We work just as hard,

188
00:15:22,145 --> 00:15:23,985
so the rewards-

189
00:15:24,865 --> 00:15:25,865
-must be equal too.

190
00:15:28,465 --> 00:15:29,905
Thank you.

191
00:15:31,945 --> 00:15:34,625
So the harvest from this year

192
00:15:35,665 --> 00:15:38,705
will be shared by everyone, just like before.

193
00:16:36,505 --> 00:16:37,705
Is it good?

194
00:16:38,625 --> 00:16:39,785
I haven’t tried it yet.

195
00:16:52,105 --> 00:16:55,545
What’s wrong, Comrade Ying? You look pale.

196
00:16:58,265 --> 00:16:59,905
Just a stomachache.

197
00:17:01,065 --> 00:17:03,304
Is it your period? Want me to get you medicine?

198
00:17:03,305 --> 00:17:04,944
I’ll find some for you.

199
00:17:04,945 --> 00:17:07,144
You’re really bringing this up while we’re eating?

200
00:17:07,145 --> 00:17:08,665
You’re gonna ruin everyone’s appetite.

201
00:17:09,705 --> 00:17:12,304
Period pain is no different from a headache or a fever.

202
00:17:12,305 --> 00:17:13,745
What’s so disgusting about it?

203
00:17:16,665 --> 00:17:18,504
Are you okay?

204
00:17:18,505 --> 00:17:20,345
Do you get this every month?

205
00:17:22,265 --> 00:17:24,065
My period hasn’t come for five or six months.

206
00:17:24,585 --> 00:17:25,585
Five or six months!?

207
00:17:26,865 --> 00:17:28,225
Maybe you should see a doctor.

208
00:17:29,065 --> 00:17:31,025
How does it not come for that long?

209
00:17:31,985 --> 00:17:33,465
You’re not taking care of yourself.

210
00:17:34,265 --> 00:17:35,345
Why are you scolding me?

211
00:17:36,065 --> 00:17:37,664
Because I care.

212
00:17:37,665 --> 00:17:38,825
If this is how you care,

213
00:17:39,425 --> 00:17:40,945
then don’t.

214
00:17:48,105 --> 00:17:49,505
What’s going on here?

215
00:17:51,185 --> 00:17:53,264
We may have raised our voices,

216
00:17:53,265 --> 00:17:55,704
but we’re not fighting or causing trouble.

217
00:17:55,705 --> 00:17:57,704
Loud but not fighting?

218
00:17:57,705 --> 00:17:59,385
Who’s going to believe that?

219
00:18:00,505 --> 00:18:02,905
Everyone here saw you two arguing.

220
00:18:05,545 --> 00:18:07,945
This is exactly why the Three Delays policy exists.

221
00:18:08,625 --> 00:18:10,345
Love only causes problems.

222
00:18:10,905 --> 00:18:12,865
When people fall out, they can’t work together.

223
00:18:14,585 --> 00:18:16,384
If you’d just let the two of them talk it out,

224
00:18:16,385 --> 00:18:17,864
it would’ve been over already.

225
00:18:17,865 --> 00:18:21,105
Instead, outsiders turn small issues into big ones.

226
00:18:24,465 --> 00:18:26,464
That loud argument still wasn’t big enough for you?

227
00:18:26,465 --> 00:18:28,545
You know fighting isn’t allowed here.

228
00:18:29,745 --> 00:18:31,824
This needs to be punished, Comrade Ploeng.

229
00:18:31,825 --> 00:18:33,744
So others don’t follow this example.

230
00:18:33,745 --> 00:18:36,424
I think you two should stop doing mass work.

231
00:18:36,425 --> 00:18:38,665
You’d be better off farming instead.

232
00:18:39,705 --> 00:18:42,704
No, sir—I’m better suited for mass work.

233
00:18:42,705 --> 00:18:44,785
I still have many articles to write.

234
00:18:47,345 --> 00:18:51,224
Comrade Fah, what are you basing your judgment on?

235
00:18:51,225 --> 00:18:52,904
This is our first offense.

236
00:18:52,905 --> 00:18:54,824
We’ve never done anything wrong before.

237
00:18:54,825 --> 00:18:56,705
A warning should be enough.

238
00:18:59,785 --> 00:19:01,265
Alright alright alright,

239
00:19:02,585 --> 00:19:03,585
that’s enough.

240
00:19:06,865 --> 00:19:10,184
This is your first time causing a disturbance.

241
00:19:10,185 --> 00:19:11,864
I won’t punish you.

242
00:19:11,865 --> 00:19:13,545
But if it happens again,

243
00:19:14,545 --> 00:19:16,305
it won’t just be a warning.

244
00:19:18,345 --> 00:19:20,465
Alright, dismissed.

245
00:19:26,465 --> 00:19:27,465
Hey!

246
00:19:50,745 --> 00:19:52,305
You little troublemaker.

247
00:19:53,185 --> 00:19:54,305
What, Comrade Yue?

248
00:19:54,865 --> 00:19:55,865
What troublemaker?

249
00:19:57,385 --> 00:19:58,544
Oh—.

250
00:19:58,545 --> 00:20:00,945
The wound. It troubles me.

251
00:20:09,025 --> 00:20:12,385
Comrade Ying! Comrade Ying! Comrade Ying!

252
00:20:13,585 --> 00:20:14,585
Let go of me.

253
00:20:16,425 --> 00:20:17,585
I’m sorry…

254
00:20:18,705 --> 00:20:20,305
for raising my voice at you earlier.

255
00:20:21,065 --> 00:20:23,064
It’s just that you don’t take care of yourself.

256
00:20:23,065 --> 00:20:24,825
I can’t help but worry.

257
00:20:26,265 --> 00:20:28,505
It’s messing with my focus at work.

258
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:31,545
You should try to understand me too.

259
00:20:34,265 --> 00:20:35,265
Yes,

260
00:20:35,665 --> 00:20:37,345
we should prioritize work and ideology.

261
00:20:38,145 --> 00:20:39,305
Love comes second.

262
00:20:41,265 --> 00:20:42,905
Then let’s make it clear.

263
00:20:43,625 --> 00:20:46,025
We already disagree on so many things anyway.

264
00:20:50,025 --> 00:20:51,025
What do you mean?

265
00:20:59,905 --> 00:21:01,344
Let’s break up.

266
00:21:01,345 --> 00:21:03,265
Hey—what the hell?

267
00:21:37,465 --> 00:21:38,705
Haha!

268
00:21:41,145 --> 00:21:42,425
Hahahaha.

269
00:21:43,305 --> 00:21:46,585
I am the god of cockscomb flowers!

270
00:21:47,425 --> 00:21:50,784
Today, I grant Comrade Ying one wish!

271
00:21:50,785 --> 00:21:55,625
You get one wish.

272
00:22:05,465 --> 00:22:07,424
- Come on, Comrade Ying.
- Hurry up!

273
00:22:07,425 --> 00:22:08,984
I’m getting tired here.

274
00:22:08,985 --> 00:22:11,625
So tired—help me!

275
00:22:18,265 --> 00:22:20,105
I wish that the person I love-

276
00:22:21,665 --> 00:22:23,224
-will never make me cry again.

277
00:22:23,225 --> 00:22:26,224
Ah hahaha.

278
00:22:26,225 --> 00:22:32,505
Then I grant your wish. May it come true.

279
00:22:33,825 --> 00:22:36,625
Alright, stop crying—get up.

280
00:22:37,825 --> 00:22:39,344
Come on, up you go.

281
00:22:39,345 --> 00:22:41,545
Let’s dance.

282
00:24:08,065 --> 00:24:09,385
What’s wrong with you?

283
00:24:10,305 --> 00:24:11,305
I’m fine.

284
00:24:12,385 --> 00:24:14,545
You’re the one who’s not.

285
00:24:15,465 --> 00:24:16,465
Huh?

286
00:24:18,465 --> 00:24:19,465
Right here.

287
00:24:23,705 --> 00:24:26,865
Oh—it’s nothing. It’ll heal.

288
00:24:28,025 --> 00:24:30,465
That’s exactly why I want to treat it.

289
00:24:34,825 --> 00:24:36,065
You don't need to.

290
00:25:02,105 --> 00:25:06,385
Just knowing you care is enough.

291
00:25:17,865 --> 00:25:19,345
Does it still hurt?

292
00:25:22,945 --> 00:25:25,705
Ouch—yeah, it hurts.

293
00:25:26,585 --> 00:25:27,905
Still hurts?

294
00:25:39,665 --> 00:25:40,705
Comrade Roong!

295
00:25:43,905 --> 00:25:44,905
Comrade Roong!

296
00:25:48,665 --> 00:25:49,744
Is Comrade Roong not here?

297
00:25:49,745 --> 00:25:51,025
Comrade Ploeng called a meeting.

298
00:25:53,985 --> 00:25:55,145
Oh,

299
00:25:57,305 --> 00:25:59,305
they went to the villagers’ area.

300
00:26:00,945 --> 00:26:03,465
Comrade Yue too. Comrade Ploeng is waiting.

301
00:26:04,225 --> 00:26:05,225
Oh.

302
00:26:31,105 --> 00:26:32,505
Don’t forget to apply the medicine.

303
00:26:43,865 --> 00:26:45,624
Comrade, move the stuff to the platform.

304
00:26:45,625 --> 00:26:46,625
Okay.

305
00:26:52,305 --> 00:26:53,625
Careful.

306
00:26:56,425 --> 00:26:58,384
There are more weapons this time than usual.

307
00:26:58,385 --> 00:26:59,865
Are we preparing for a big operation?

308
00:27:00,345 --> 00:27:01,905
Uh… where?

309
00:27:03,265 --> 00:27:04,824
Why are you asking?

310
00:27:04,825 --> 00:27:06,425
You’re usually not interested in combat.

311
00:27:07,065 --> 00:27:08,065
- Um...
- Yaguar,

312
00:27:08,665 --> 00:27:09,945
come help carry this crate.

313
00:27:21,025 --> 00:27:23,065
Achoo! Achoo!

314
00:27:23,825 --> 00:27:25,344
Allergies are acting up again, Aren't they?

315
00:27:25,345 --> 00:27:27,264
How are you going to fight like that?

316
00:27:27,265 --> 00:27:28,504
I’m not going.

317
00:27:28,505 --> 00:27:30,065
Comrade Ploeng told me to stay at base.

318
00:27:34,265 --> 00:27:35,425
Then sit down and rest.

319
00:27:36,665 --> 00:27:38,185
It’s fine—there are plenty of people.

320
00:27:48,985 --> 00:27:49,985
You don’t look well—.

321
00:27:50,705 --> 00:27:51,865
You’ve been sneezing nonstop.

322
00:27:57,385 --> 00:27:58,865
I’ll roll you some herbal cigarettes.

323
00:27:59,985 --> 00:28:01,385
I don’t smoke.

324
00:28:02,585 --> 00:28:04,665
Mine help with allergies.

325
00:28:09,465 --> 00:28:12,225
Since when did you care about me?

326
00:28:19,665 --> 00:28:21,305
Do I look like I don’t?

327
00:28:26,185 --> 00:28:27,585
Has anyone seen Comrade Bai Tong?

328
00:28:30,105 --> 00:28:32,465
I heard Comrade Ploeng is taking her for shooting practice.

329
00:28:33,145 --> 00:28:34,145
Is something wrong?

330
00:28:35,705 --> 00:28:37,624
Then can you check over there?

331
00:28:37,625 --> 00:28:39,425
Looks like the supply delivery is incomplete.

332
00:28:56,625 --> 00:29:00,864
One more time—steady hands, raise your shoulders.

333
00:29:00,865 --> 00:29:02,344
Grip tight.

334
00:29:02,345 --> 00:29:03,345
Ready…

335
00:29:04,705 --> 00:29:05,705
Go.

336
00:29:05,865 --> 00:29:06,905
Yay!

337
00:29:07,745 --> 00:29:08,625
Yay!

338
00:29:08,626 --> 00:29:10,304
Yay! This is fun, Dad!

339
00:29:10,305 --> 00:29:15,265
Good job—that’s my girl!

340
00:29:16,785 --> 00:29:17,905
Remember this—.

341
00:29:19,065 --> 00:29:20,105
I’m not training you-

342
00:29:20,945 --> 00:29:22,305
-just for fun.

343
00:29:23,025 --> 00:29:26,065
You need to learn to protect yourself in case I’m not around.

344
00:29:26,745 --> 00:29:28,504
So you can take care of yourself.

345
00:29:28,505 --> 00:29:29,625
Do you understand?

346
00:29:30,265 --> 00:29:33,385
Do you have to go fight again? Can’t you stay?

347
00:29:40,545 --> 00:29:41,545
My girl,

348
00:29:42,625 --> 00:29:43,825
you're already well aware

349
00:29:44,985 --> 00:29:47,825
that I have a duty, just like everyone else,

350
00:29:48,665 --> 00:29:50,825
to protect this base so everyone here can live safely.

351
00:29:52,105 --> 00:29:54,224
Comrade Ying told me

352
00:29:54,225 --> 00:29:56,465
that people outside don’t have to carry guns and fight.

353
00:29:57,545 --> 00:29:59,225
Cause if we win,

354
00:30:00,625 --> 00:30:03,025
then we won’t have to carry guns anymore.

355
00:30:04,425 --> 00:30:08,705
No matter where we are, we won’t have to fight again.

356
00:30:10,305 --> 00:30:13,065
You’ll get to live like a normal child.

357
00:30:13,865 --> 00:30:16,065
I want to see what the outside world is like.

358
00:30:16,665 --> 00:30:19,425
Please bring victory and take me there, dad.

359
00:30:24,705 --> 00:30:26,265
That's a deal, my girl.

360
00:30:43,105 --> 00:30:44,305
Yaguar.

361
00:30:50,345 --> 00:30:51,345
Here—.

362
00:30:51,705 --> 00:30:53,665
Comrade Roong asked me to give you this medicine.

363
00:30:54,545 --> 00:30:55,545
Thank you.

364
00:31:05,185 --> 00:31:07,505
She’s already requested more from HQ.

365
00:31:09,665 --> 00:31:10,665
Hang in there for now.

366
00:31:12,745 --> 00:31:13,865
You like him that much, huh?

367
00:31:14,385 --> 00:31:16,064
Is that why you broke up with me?

368
00:31:16,065 --> 00:31:16,665
Comrade Gaun Hin.

369
00:31:16,666 --> 00:31:17,944
- You like him that much?
- Comrade Gaun Hin.

370
00:31:17,945 --> 00:31:19,224
What does he have that I don’t?!

371
00:31:19,225 --> 00:31:20,225
Sila.

372
00:31:20,665 --> 00:31:21,825
That’s enough, Sila. Stop it.

373
00:31:25,025 --> 00:31:26,264
You like him that much, huh?!

374
00:31:26,265 --> 00:31:27,944
Comrade Ying just brought me medicine.

375
00:31:27,945 --> 00:31:28,945
Don’t get the wrong idea.

376
00:31:29,425 --> 00:31:30,385
Do you know-

377
00:31:30,386 --> 00:31:32,704
-how much she cried because of you?

378
00:31:32,705 --> 00:31:33,945
It took her so long to stop.

379
00:31:36,905 --> 00:31:38,905
Please don’t hurt her again.

380
00:31:40,345 --> 00:31:41,345
Yaguar.

381
00:31:43,265 --> 00:31:44,705
Go take the medicine to your mother.

382
00:32:18,225 --> 00:32:19,624
What are you going to do with those 'Cork tree' flowers,

383
00:32:19,625 --> 00:32:20,625
Comrade Yue?

384
00:32:22,025 --> 00:32:23,345
Comrade Saeng has allergies.

385
00:32:32,665 --> 00:32:34,481
His nose has turned red from sneezing non-stop.

386
00:32:34,505 --> 00:32:37,145
If he’s not feeling well, just get him medicine.

387
00:32:38,065 --> 00:32:39,625
Why do you even have to do all this?

388
00:32:40,945 --> 00:32:42,265
I want to do it myself.

389
00:32:45,825 --> 00:32:47,064
It's on your neck like this and if you can still lose it-

390
00:32:47,065 --> 00:32:48,264
-then I'll be speechless.

391
00:32:48,265 --> 00:32:49,785
Not losing it anymore.

392
00:32:51,265 --> 00:32:52,305
Then let me help.

393
00:32:53,265 --> 00:32:54,625
It’s okay, Comrade Roong.

394
00:32:55,305 --> 00:32:57,305
You’ve been taking care of patients all day.

395
00:33:01,185 --> 00:33:02,185
Go get some rest.

396
00:33:05,065 --> 00:33:06,984
Hey, what are you waiting for?

397
00:33:06,985 --> 00:33:09,544
I’ll catch up. You two go ahead. I’m not that hungry yet.

398
00:33:09,545 --> 00:33:11,185
Alright.

399
00:33:21,265 --> 00:33:22,745
That should do.

400
00:33:56,945 --> 00:33:58,345
Where are you wandering off to?

401
00:34:08,385 --> 00:34:10,824
The day we transported weapons,

402
00:34:10,825 --> 00:34:12,585
I noticed Yagaur acting strange.

403
00:34:14,065 --> 00:34:15,665
Ask Comrade Roong to keep an eye on him.

404
00:34:20,345 --> 00:34:22,105
And what about you and Comrade Yue?

405
00:34:25,465 --> 00:34:27,145
I saw you two talking for a while earlier.

406
00:34:32,305 --> 00:34:33,625
Well,

407
00:34:35,985 --> 00:34:37,385
It’s nothing.

408
00:34:44,185 --> 00:34:45,665
You still like him, don’t you?

409
00:34:51,585 --> 00:34:53,344
It’s been years already.

410
00:34:53,345 --> 00:34:54,504
You should know by now—.

411
00:34:54,505 --> 00:34:56,265
He only sees you as a younger sister.

412
00:35:00,465 --> 00:35:02,705
If he liked you, he would’ve shown it by now.

413
00:35:04,905 --> 00:35:06,545
I’m saying this because I care about you.

414
00:35:07,425 --> 00:35:09,025
I don’t want to see you get hurt again.

415
00:35:15,065 --> 00:35:17,424
If that’s all you had to day,

416
00:35:17,425 --> 00:35:19,825
I’ll get back to work.

417
00:35:34,825 --> 00:35:35,825
Have you figured it out.

418
00:35:36,305 --> 00:35:38,905
Why HQ sent weapons to Baan Saeng Dao base?

419
00:35:41,705 --> 00:35:44,865
Comrade Ploeng is preparing to seize a military stronghold.

420
00:35:47,225 --> 00:35:48,225
Which one?

421
00:35:50,425 --> 00:35:51,425
It's..

422
00:35:52,505 --> 00:35:54,184
The closest base.

423
00:35:54,185 --> 00:35:55,265
Right…

424
00:35:58,185 --> 00:35:59,225
By the way,

425
00:36:00,985 --> 00:36:02,465
do you know the person in this photo?

426
00:36:07,905 --> 00:36:09,345
That’s Comrade Saeng.

427
00:36:10,785 --> 00:36:13,584
You know him too? Which base is he at?

428
00:36:13,585 --> 00:36:14,825
He's with Baan Saeng Dao base.

429
00:36:15,625 --> 00:36:16,744
He’s the one who took down-

430
00:36:16,745 --> 00:36:18,145
-the commander of Baan Prongdong.

431
00:36:24,905 --> 00:36:27,105
Is something wrong?

432
00:36:33,345 --> 00:36:34,545
In a few days,

433
00:36:35,225 --> 00:36:38,105
I’ll have someone take your mother to a hospital in the city.

434
00:36:39,905 --> 00:36:41,945
Don’t worry—I’ll handle everything.

435
00:36:42,945 --> 00:36:45,144
Just find out what I asked for—.

436
00:36:45,145 --> 00:36:46,825
And everything about Comrade Saeng.

437
00:36:48,865 --> 00:36:50,585
Tell me everything you know.

438
00:37:20,065 --> 00:37:21,105
Why did you call me here?

439
00:37:26,145 --> 00:37:28,105
Hey—hey—!

440
00:37:30,465 --> 00:37:32,265
You’ll alert the whole base at this rate.

441
00:37:34,665 --> 00:37:37,025
Sneaking up on me like that scared me.

442
00:37:37,905 --> 00:37:39,265
You’re the one who called me here.

443
00:37:39,505 --> 00:37:41,945
Or not? I’ll head back then.

444
00:37:44,425 --> 00:37:45,425
Come with me.

445
00:38:05,225 --> 00:38:06,265
If you wanted to stargaze,

446
00:38:07,065 --> 00:38:08,385
why not ask Comrade Roong?

447
00:38:09,385 --> 00:38:10,505
Why me?

448
00:38:12,065 --> 00:38:13,625
I didn’t want to stargaze.

449
00:38:15,625 --> 00:38:18,345
And even if I did, it wouldn’t be with Comrade Roong.

450
00:38:47,745 --> 00:38:50,705
What’s that smell? It’s nice.

451
00:38:51,865 --> 00:38:54,945
Cork tree' flower cigarettes—they help with allergies.

452
00:38:56,985 --> 00:38:58,184
Try it.

453
00:38:58,185 --> 00:38:59,584
I don’t smoke.

454
00:38:59,585 --> 00:39:01,705
Just try—I’ll show you.

455
00:39:07,025 --> 00:39:08,025
Inhale.

456
00:39:11,465 --> 00:39:12,465
A bit deeper.

457
00:39:17,025 --> 00:39:18,425
How is it?

458
00:39:19,465 --> 00:39:22,225
It’s nice… smells good.

459
00:39:24,705 --> 00:39:27,064
Ew—why didn’t you roll a new one?

460
00:39:27,065 --> 00:39:30,305
This one has my saliva on it. Make another.

461
00:39:37,385 --> 00:39:38,545
Beautiful stars, aren't they?

462
00:39:40,025 --> 00:39:41,585
So who did you roll that for?

463
00:39:48,265 --> 00:39:51,465
Even though we’re at base, I can’t show it openly.

464
00:39:53,025 --> 00:39:54,785
But that doesn’t mean I don’t feel anything.

465
00:39:59,745 --> 00:40:00,905
Feel what?

466
00:40:05,825 --> 00:40:08,305
That you’re very special to me.

467
00:40:11,985 --> 00:40:13,505
And I want to take care of you.

468
00:40:21,225 --> 00:40:22,225
Not mad anymore?

469
00:40:25,065 --> 00:40:26,065
Ahh.

470
00:40:27,025 --> 00:40:29,305
I wasn’t mad to begin with.

471
00:40:33,065 --> 00:40:34,065
Look at my cigarette?

472
00:40:34,865 --> 00:40:37,224
It’s still half left, and youou kicked it away—

473
00:40:37,225 --> 00:40:38,465
I worked hard rolling that one.

474
00:40:40,305 --> 00:40:42,345
Forget it… The stars… let’s just watch the stars.

475
00:40:52,385 --> 00:40:54,384
Comrades, victory belongs to the people.

476
00:40:54,385 --> 00:40:56,024
Comrades, victory belongs to the people.
- This time,

477
00:40:56,025 --> 00:40:58,905
we fight 'til the end. They have guns

478
00:40:59,745 --> 00:41:01,624
we have guns.

479
00:41:01,625 --> 00:41:04,265
And we will never bow to anyone.

480
00:41:05,745 --> 00:41:06,985
If we fight,

481
00:41:08,025 --> 00:41:09,944
we fight together.

482
00:41:09,945 --> 00:41:11,425
And if we die,

483
00:41:12,465 --> 00:41:15,905
I will die beside all of you—my comrades.

484
00:41:17,345 --> 00:41:21,424
And this time, we will return with victory.

485
00:41:21,425 --> 00:41:26,824
And we’ll celebrate that victory on our Party’s anniversary.

486
00:41:26,825 --> 00:41:28,864
Yes, sir—I'm already preparing the celebration.

487
00:41:28,865 --> 00:41:31,225
Yay!

488
00:41:32,305 --> 00:41:33,664
I’ll be a good girl.

489
00:41:33,665 --> 00:41:35,705
I won’t be naughty. Come back soon, Dad.

490
00:41:36,705 --> 00:41:39,065
Good girl. I love you.

491
00:41:55,505 --> 00:41:58,185
Comrades, are you ready?

492
00:41:58,585 --> 00:41:59,585
Ready!

493
00:42:00,745 --> 00:42:01,505
Will we fight?

494
00:42:01,505 --> 00:42:02,505
Fight!

495
00:42:05,745 --> 00:42:06,745
Fight!

496
00:42:18,225 --> 00:42:20,104
Let’s do this!

497
00:42:20,105 --> 00:42:26,985
Fight! Fight!

498
00:42:57,505 --> 00:42:59,024
(Explosion)

499
00:42:59,025 --> 00:42:59,825
Go!

500
00:42:59,826 --> 00:43:01,185
Comrades. Go!

501
00:43:04,665 --> 00:43:06,305
Their base is ours tonight!

